  "schema_name": "eywa_node_response",
  "schema_version": "v1",
  "orchestration_decision": "delegate",
  "decision_notes": "The problem asks for the minimum number of set bits in the product of 2023 and n. This is equivalent to finding the minimum Hamming weight of a multiple of 2023. Since 2023 is not a power of 2, we look for the smallest number of ones that can form a multiple of 2023.",
  "helpers": [
    {
      "label": "helper_1",
      "instructions": "Determine the prime factorization of 2023 and check if it is coprime to 2. Then, investigate the properties of the number 2023 in relation to the sum of powers of 2. Specifically, check if there exists a number of the form 2^a + 2^b + ... (with minimum terms) that is divisible by 2023 by testing small values of k for the equation sum_{i=1}^k 2^{a_i} = 0 mod 2023."
    },
    {
      "label": "helper_2",
      "instructions": "Verify if k(n) = 1 is possible (requires 2023 to be a power of 2, which it is not). Verify if k(n) = 2 is possible (requires 2^a + 2^b to be a multiple of 2023, or 2^a(2^{b-a} + 1) to be a multiple of 2023). If k(n) = 2 is impossible, test if k(n) = 3 is possible by checking if there exist integers a, b, c such that 2^a + 2^b + 2^c is a multiple of 2023."
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "The parent agent will take the results from helper_1 and helper_2 to determine the smallest integer k such that a sum of k powers of 2 is divisible by 2023. If helper_2 confirms k=1 and k=2 are impossible and finds a solution for k=3, the answer is 3. If k=3 is also impossible, the agent will evaluate the next smallest k."
}

